column2: SSH agent support for git and svn integrations

column3: This version allows SSH agent-based authentication to be used for authenticating to SVN or git, as discussed in the ticket http://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-52034
A contributor agreement has been submitted by Doug Grey, VP of Engineering at at Indeed.com (which owns copyright to this change).
Sorry for delay with this pull request.

@charles-dyfis-net I see that SvnKit 1.7.10 introduced SSH agent support added via JSCH library. Was it your patch accepted by SvnKit team or it is somewhat different?
Currently there are no reasons (besides additional testing) not to update SvnKit shipped with IDEA to 1.7.11, so we'd prefer an official build to the patched version.
Could you please check if the patch works fine if SvnKit 1.7.11 is used?
Yes, this patch works with upstream SVNKit 1.7.11.

@charles-dyfis-net
Thanks! Could you please recreate the pull request without patching svnkit?
Per request.
That said, there's still a pretty nontrivial set of conflicts trying to merge this into current master -- one of the perils of leaving something unmerged for quite this long.
I might try to rebase. Would master be the appropriate target?
Yep. Please rebase against current master.

Done. I'm including the upgrade to SVNKit 1.7.11 (released version) as a separate changeset -- so y'all can cherry-pick the piece that doesn't contain it if the upgrade has been done separately. As the patch can't be built without an appropriate SVNKit, not including one at all doesn't make much sense.
Bleh -- this PR is still using 129 as target. Closing and recreating.
